{
  "texts": [
    "This is discussed in the section 'Estimates for magic-state yield'.",
    "Articlesection 'Analysis in terms of single-gate errors' using the results of the error-suppressed scheme without any post-selection.",
    "Assuming an uncorrelated error model, we find that the average probability per single-error event is 0.19% with a standard deviation of 0.11%.",
    "The single most-likely error event occurs with probability 1.2%.",
    "This event corresponds to an error occurring during the X stabilizer measurement that spreads to and is detected by a flag qubit."
  ]
}